net.tmachine.gpg4.gameserver
Class RequestProcessor

java.lang.Object
  net.tmachine.gpg4.bModule
      net.tmachine.gpg4.gameserver.RequestProcessor
All Implemented Interfaces:
iModule, iRequestProcessor, java.lang.Runnable
public class RequestProcessor
extends bModule
implements iRequestProcessor, iModule, java.lang.Runnable

This is a very simple example of a PROCESSing stage which merely loads a single HTML file from disk and serves it to any web-browsers that connect.

It caches the page in memory using the FileManager class - note: this is NOT the same as caching responses to requests; this is a lower-level form of caching (see website for more details of different caching levels)

See Also:
FileManager
